---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service - MapMyRoots"
  description="MapMyRoots terms of service. Read the terms and conditions for using our free family tree builder application."
  canonicalPath="/terms"
>
    <div class="legal-container">
      <div class="legal-header">
        <h1 data-i18n="terms.title">Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="last-updated" data-i18n="terms.last_updated">Last Updated: January 1, 2025</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-content">
        <div class="highlight-box">
          <p data-i18n="terms.intro"><strong>Welcome to MapMyRoots!</strong> These terms outline your rights and responsibilities when using our free family tree builder. By using our Service, you agree to these terms.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 data-i18n="terms.acceptance.title">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p data-i18n="terms.acceptance.content">By accessing and using MapMyRoots ("Service"), you accept and agree to be bound by the terms and provision of this agreement. If you do not agree to these Terms of Service, please do not use the Service.</p>

        <h2 data-i18n="terms.description.title">2. Description of Service</h2>
        <p data-i18n="terms.description.intro">MapMyRoots provides a free, web-based family tree builder that allows users to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li data-i18n="terms.description.create">Create and visualize family trees</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.description.store">Store family member information locally on their device</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.description.export">Export family tree data in various formats</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.description.customize">Customize and style family trees</li>
        </ul>
        <p data-i18n="terms.description.free">The Service is provided completely free of charge with no premium features or subscriptions.</p>

        <h2 data-i18n="terms.account.title">3. No Account Required</h2>
        <p data-i18n="terms.account.content">MapMyRoots does not require users to create an account. All family tree data is stored locally on your device using browser LocalStorage. You are responsible for backing up your data by exporting it regularly.</p>

        <h2 data-i18n="terms.acceptable_use.title">4. Acceptable Use</h2>

        <h3 data-i18n="terms.acceptable_use.permitted.title">4.1 Permitted Use</h3>
        <p data-i18n="terms.acceptable_use.permitted.content">You may use the Service for any lawful purpose related to creating and managing family trees, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li data-i18n="terms.acceptable_use.permitted.personal">Personal family history research</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.acceptable_use.permitted.education">Educational projects</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.acceptable_use.permitted.reunions">Family reunions and events</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.acceptable_use.permitted.preservation">Preserving family history</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 data-i18n="terms.acceptable_use.prohibited.title">4.2 Prohibited Use</h3>
        <p data-i18n="terms.acceptable_use.prohibited.intro">You agree NOT to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li data-i18n="terms.acceptable_use.prohibited.harm">Use the Service in any way that could damage, disable, or impair the Service</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.acceptable_use.prohibited.unauthorized">Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any part of the Service</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.acceptable_use.prohibited.interfere">Interfere with or disrupt the Service or servers</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.acceptable_use.prohibited.automated">Use automated systems to access the Service in a way that sends more requests than a human could reasonably produce</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.acceptable_use.prohibited.reverse">Reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble any part of the Service</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.acceptable_use.prohibited.violate">Violate any applicable laws or regulations</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.acceptable_use.prohibited.infringe">Infringe on intellectual property rights of others</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 data-i18n="terms.data_ownership.title">5. Data Ownership and Responsibility</h2>

        <h3 data-i18n="terms.data_ownership.your_data.title">5.1 Your Data</h3>
        <p data-i18n="terms.data_ownership.your_data.content">You retain all rights to the family tree data you create. Since data is stored locally on your device:</p>
        <ul>
          <li data-i18n="terms.data_ownership.your_data.ownership">You own all family tree data you create</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.data_ownership.your_data.control">You have complete control over your data</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.data_ownership.your_data.responsibility">You are responsible for the accuracy of information you input</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.data_ownership.your_data.backup">You are responsible for backing up your data</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.data_ownership.your_data.loss">We are not liable for any data loss</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 data-i18n="terms.data_ownership.privacy.title">5.2 Privacy and Personal Information</h3>
        <p data-i18n="terms.data_ownership.privacy.content">You are responsible for ensuring you have the right to use and share any personal information about individuals in your family tree. Please respect privacy rights and obtain appropriate consent when sharing family trees containing personal information about living individuals.</p>

        <h2 data-i18n="terms.intellectual_property.title">6. Intellectual Property</h2>

        <h3 data-i18n="terms.intellectual_property.our.title">6.1 Our IP</h3>
        <p data-i18n="terms.intellectual_property.our.content">The Service, including its design, code, graphics, and user interface, is owned by MapMyRoots and protected by copyright, trademark, and other intellectual property laws. You may not copy, modify, or distribute any part of the Service without permission.</p>

        <h3 data-i18n="terms.intellectual_property.open_source.title">6.2 Open Source</h3>
        <p data-i18n="terms.intellectual_property.open_source.content">Certain components of the Service may be subject to open source licenses. These components are provided under their respective open source licenses.</p>

        <h2 data-i18n="terms.disclaimers.title">7. Disclaimers and Limitations of Liability</h2>

        <h3 data-i18n="terms.disclaimers.as_is.title">7.1 "As Is" Service</h3>
        <p data-i18n="terms.disclaimers.as_is.content">THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE" WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EITHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, OR NON-INFRINGEMENT.</p>

        <h3 data-i18n="terms.disclaimers.no_guarantee.title">7.2 No Guarantee</h3>
        <p data-i18n="terms.disclaimers.no_guarantee.content">We do not guarantee that:</p>
        <ul>
          <li data-i18n="terms.disclaimers.no_guarantee.uninterrupted">The Service will be uninterrupted or error-free</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.disclaimers.no_guarantee.bugs">All bugs or errors will be corrected</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.disclaimers.no_guarantee.secure">The Service is completely secure or free from viruses</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.disclaimers.no_guarantee.accuracy">Results will be accurate or reliable</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 data-i18n="terms.disclaimers.liability.title">7.3 Limitation of Liability</h3>
        <p data-i18n="terms.disclaimers.liability.content">TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, MAPMYROOTS SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, OR ANY LOSS OF PROFITS OR REVENUES, WHETHER INCURRED DIRECTLY OR INDIRECTLY, OR ANY LOSS OF DATA, USE, GOODWILL, OR OTHER INTANGIBLE LOSSES RESULTING FROM:</p>
        <ul>
          <li data-i18n="terms.disclaimers.liability.access">Your access to or use of or inability to access or use the Service</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.disclaimers.liability.third_party">Any conduct or content of any third party</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.disclaimers.liability.unauthorized">Any unauthorized access, use, or alteration of your data</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 data-i18n="terms.data_loss.title">8. Data Loss</h2>
        <p data-i18n="terms.data_loss.content">Since your family tree data is stored locally on your device, we cannot recover lost data. Data may be lost if you:</p>
        <ul>
          <li data-i18n="terms.data_loss.clear">Clear your browser's cache or LocalStorage</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.data_loss.uninstall">Uninstall your browser</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.data_loss.device">Experience device failure or corruption</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.data_loss.reset">Reset your device to factory settings</li>
        </ul>
        <p data-i18n="terms.data_loss.backup"><strong>Important:</strong> Regularly export and backup your family tree data to prevent loss.</p>

        <h2 data-i18n="terms.availability.title">9. Service Availability</h2>
        <p data-i18n="terms.availability.content">We strive to provide continuous access to the Service, but we do not guarantee uninterrupted availability. The Service may be temporarily unavailable due to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li data-i18n="terms.availability.maintenance">Scheduled maintenance</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.availability.technical">Technical difficulties</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.availability.circumstances">Circumstances beyond our control</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 data-i18n="terms.modifications.title">10. Modifications to Service and Terms</h2>

        <h3 data-i18n="terms.modifications.service.title">10.1 Service Changes</h3>
        <p data-i18n="terms.modifications.service.content">We reserve the right to modify, suspend, or discontinue any part of the Service at any time without notice. We are not liable to you or any third party for any modification, suspension, or discontinuation of the Service.</p>

        <h3 data-i18n="terms.modifications.terms.title">10.2 Terms Changes</h3>
        <p data-i18n="terms.modifications.terms.content">We may update these Terms of Service from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by updating the "Last Updated" date. Your continued use of the Service after changes constitutes acceptance of the new terms.</p>

        <h2 data-i18n="terms.termination.title">11. Termination</h2>
        <p data-i18n="terms.termination.content">We reserve the right to terminate or suspend access to the Service immediately, without prior notice, for any reason, including but not limited to breach of these Terms. Since no account is required, termination would involve blocking access from specific IP addresses or implementing other technical restrictions.</p>

        <h2 data-i18n="terms.external_links.title">12. External Links</h2>
        <p data-i18n="terms.external_links.content">The Service may contain links to third-party websites or services. We are not responsible for the content, privacy policies, or practices of third-party websites. You access third-party websites at your own risk.</p>

        <h2 data-i18n="terms.indemnification.title">13. Indemnification</h2>
        <p data-i18n="terms.indemnification.content">You agree to indemnify and hold harmless MapMyRoots, its affiliates, and their respective officers, directors, employees, and agents from any claims, damages, losses, liabilities, and expenses (including legal fees) arising out of:</p>
        <ul>
          <li data-i18n="terms.indemnification.use">Your use of the Service</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.indemnification.violation">Your violation of these Terms</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.indemnification.rights">Your violation of any rights of another party</li>
          <li data-i18n="terms.indemnification.content">Content you create or share using the Service</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 data-i18n="terms.governing_law.title">14. Governing Law</h2>
        <p data-i18n="terms.governing_law.content">These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with applicable laws, without regard to conflict of law provisions. Any disputes arising from these Terms or the Service shall be resolved in accordance with applicable jurisdiction.</p>

        <h2 data-i18n="terms.severability.title">15. Severability</h2>
        <p data-i18n="terms.severability.content">If any provision of these Terms is found to be invalid or unenforceable, the remaining provisions will remain in full force and effect.</p>

        <h2 data-i18n="terms.entire_agreement.title">16. Entire Agreement</h2>
        <p data-i18n="terms.entire_agreement.content">These Terms of Service, together with our Privacy Policy, constitute the entire agreement between you and MapMyRoots regarding the use of the Service.</p>

        <div class="contact-info">
          <h2 data-i18n="terms.contact.title">17. Contact Information</h2>
          <p data-i18n="terms.contact.intro">If you have any questions about these Terms of Service, please contact us:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong data-i18n="terms.contact.email_label">Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@mapmyroots.com">support@mapmyroots.com</a></li>
            <li><strong data-i18n="terms.contact.website_label">Website:</strong> <a href="https://mapmyroots.com">mapmyroots.com</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="highlight-box">
          <p data-i18n="terms.thank_you"><strong>Thank you for using MapMyRoots!</strong> We're committed to providing a free, privacy-focused tool for preserving family history. By using our Service, you agree to these terms and our commitment to keeping your data private and secure on your device.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
</BaseLayout>
